# Permissions Rules (V2.1)

**Authority:** `00_architecture_authority.mdc` · **Detail:** `doc/ARCHITECTURE_V2_AGENT_RULES.md`

## Source of truth

| Edit | Generated (never edit) |
|------|------------------------|
| `shared/rbac/permissions.ts` | `backend/src/auth/permissions.ts` |
| `shared/rbac/mfaPolicy.ts` | `backend/src/auth/mfaPolicy.ts` |

After permission changes: `npm run build:backend`

Tests: `backend/src/auth/permissions.test.ts`

## Permission naming

Format: `domain.action` or `feature.subfeature.action`

Examples:

- `financial.write`
- `reports.trial_balance.read`
- `users.manage`
- `payroll.read`

Add new constants to `shared/rbac/permissions.ts` and map to roles in `buildPermissionMatrix()`.

## Backend guards

```typescript
router.post('/', requirePermission('financial.write'), async (req, res) => { ... });
router.get('/trial-balance', requirePermission('reports.trial_balance.read'), ...);
```

Additional guards:

- `requireCompanyAdmin()` — tenant admin operations
- `requireRole('accountant')` — legacy role checks (prefer permissions)
- `requirePayrollAccessForPayrollPaths()` — payroll route mount
- `requireFinancialWriteForFinancialPaths()` — GL mutation paths
- `rbacMiddleware` — method-aware checks

Mount order: `authMiddleware` → `requireActiveSubscription()` → domain guards → `requirePermission()`

## Frontend gating

```typescript
const { hasPermission } = usePermissions();
if (!hasPermission('financial.write')) return null;
```

- Hide UI actions user cannot perform
- **Backend must still enforce** — UI gating is not security

## Role summary

| Role | Typical access |
|------|----------------|
| `super_admin` | All permissions + cross-tenant admin |
| `company_admin` | Tenant admin, users, settings |
| `accountant` | Financial write, reports, audit read |
| `sales_user` | Project selling, marketing plans |
| `read_only_user` | Read reports, no writes |
| `project_manager` | Limited financial read (e.g. P&L only) |

Full matrix: `shared/rbac/permissions.ts`

## New feature checklist

1. Define permission constant(s) in `shared/rbac/permissions.ts`
2. Assign to roles in permission matrix
3. `npm run build:backend`
4. `requirePermission()` on every mutating route
5. `usePermissions()` on UI actions
6. Test with `read_only_user` and domain role (e.g. sales_user)

## Payroll & financial exceptions

- Payroll routes: `requirePayrollAccessForPayrollPaths()`
- Trial balance / GL reports: specific `reports.*.read` permissions
- Project manager: restricted financial statement access

## MUST NOT

- Hardcode role strings in routes without permission constants
- Skip backend guard because UI hides button
- Edit `backend/src/auth/permissions.ts` directly
- Grant `financial.write` without understanding GL impact

